wikipedia_page.main: Samuel Paul Osborne (born 10 January 1999) is an English professional footballer who currently plays for National League North side AFC Fylde. Osborne started his youth career at Dunkirk before moving to Notts County in 2016 where he played for four years, winning two Young Player of the Season awards in a row before moving to Warwickshire side Leamington in 2020.
